Package: contextgit
Version: 1.2.0
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: python3 (>= 3.11), python3-pip
Recommends: python3-watchdog
Maintainer: ContextGit Developers <developers@contextgit.dev>
Description: Requirements traceability for LLM-assisted development
 contextgit is a local-first, git-friendly CLI tool for managing requirements
 and context traceability in LLM-assisted software projects.
 .
 Features:
  - Tracks traceability from business needs to code to tests
  - Embeds metadata in Markdown, Python, and JavaScript/TypeScript files
  - Detects staleness via checksums
  - Provides JSON output for LLM integration
  - Automatic LLM integration setup (--setup-llm flag)
  - Impact analysis for downstream changes
  - Git hooks for automatic scanning
  - Watch mode for file monitoring
  - MCP server for native Claude Desktop integration
  - Designed for Cursor, Claude Code and similar LLM tools
